text: Gülbahar is a Turkish given name for females and may refer to: *Gülbahar Hatun, wife of Ottoman Sultan Mehmed II, and Valide Sultan as the mother or step-mother of Sultan Bayezid II *Gülbahar Hatun, wife of Ottoman Sultan Bayezid II and the mother of Sultan Selim I *Mahidevran Gülbahar Sultan, wife of Ottoman Sultan Suleiman the Magnificent and the mother of Şehzade Mustafa Category:Turkish feminine given names
title: Gülbahar
